subSubSection.paragraph:
DESCRIPTION OF THE HADJIDIMOVO MATERIAL (
FIGS 4-6
)

The metapodials are large (Annexe: 
Tables 3
; 
4
), with a cervid-like appearance, being slender and transversally compressed, but are relatively robust by comparison with the metapodials of the small- er 
Boselaphini
from Hadjidimovo, 

Miotragocerus

. The widening from diaphysis to epiphysis is smooth, without abrupt change of width. The trochlear keels are neither very prominent nor very sharp.

